description: Redevelopment to provide replacement car showroom or shops and 74 new flats comprising: basement parking, ground floor, five upper floors, part 6th and 7th floors: Second revision to current scheme including reduction of north rear wing at 1st floor level and amending boundary wall with Alvanley Gardens so that it is the same height as existing.
decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the end of five years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).
Condition : 2 - The details of all proposed materials including windows, glazing, balconies, railings, privacy screens stairs, doors, copper cladding, stone, timber, brick facing materials, render and fencing boundary wall treatments  to be used on the building shall not be otherwise than as shall have been submitted to and approved by the Council before any work is commenced. Such details shall include erection of a  sample panel board on site. 

Reason : To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the character of the immediate area in accordance with the requirements of policies EN1 and EN13  of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
Condition : 3 - No development shall take place until full details of hard and soft landscaping and means of enclosure of all un-built, open areas have been submitted to and approved by the Council. 

Reason: To enable the Council to ensure a reasonable standard of visual amenity in the scheme in accordance with the requirements of policies EN15 of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
Condition : 4 - Prior to works commencing on site, full details of privacy measures to be applied to the rear and southern flank elevations and courtyard areas shall be submitted to and approved by the Council and the development shall be carried out in accordance with such details and these shall be permanently retained and maintained. Such details shall include privacy measures such as obscure glazing , restricted window openings, high level windows, privacy screens , planting, anti climbing measures, balconies and set back of terraces as indicated on the 
drawings hereby approved.

Reason: In order to prevent unreasonable overlooking of neighbouring premises in accordance with the requirements of policies EN1 and EN19 of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
Condition : 5 - All hard and soft landscaping works shall be carried out to a reasonable standard in accordance with the approved landscape details [by not later than the end of the planting season following completion of the development or any phase of the development] [, prior to the occupation for the permitted use of the development or any phase of the development], whichever is the sooner. Any trees or areas of planting which, within a period of 5 years from the completion of the development, die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced as soon as is reasonably possible and, in any case, by not later than the end of the following planting season, with others of similar size and species, unless the Council gives written consent to any variation.

Reason: To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard of visual amenity in the scheme in accordance with the requirements of policies EN15  of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
Condition : 6 - The development shall not be occupied until the whole of the car parking  and bicycle storage provision shown on the approved drawings is provided. Thereafter the whole of the car parking and bicycle storage provision shall be retained and used for no purpose other than for the parking of vehicles of the occupiers and users of the development.

Reason: To ensure that the use of the premises does not add to parking pressures in surrounding streets which would be contrary to policies RE2 [and TR17 if residential] of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
Condition : 7 - The details of the works to the boundary wall with Alvanely Gardens shall not be otherwise than as shall have been submitted to and approved by the Council before any work is commenced on site . This  part of the development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved.

Reason: To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the character of the immediate area and privacy of adjoining occupiers in accordance with the requirements of policies EN1 , EN19 and EN13  of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
.
Condition : 8 - Notwithstanding the provisions of Article 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted  Development Order) 1995 or any Order revoking  and re-enacting that Order, no development within  Part 2 (Classes A-C) , Part 24 (Class A), Part 25 (class A-B) , Part 33 (Class A) of Schedule 2 of that Order including the erection of satellite dishes, aerials or plant shall be carried out without the grant of planning permission having first been obtained from the Council.

Reason: To safeguard the visual amenities of the area in order to ensure compliance with the requirements of policies EN1 and EN13  of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.
